A Magistrate court, sitting in Abakaliki, he Ebonyi State capital, on Tuesday remanded Bernard Oyibe, 30,  in prison for allegedly killing an 85-year-old woman, Grace Nwokwo, in the state. The suspect, was said to  have  murdered the deceased with a cutlass, on September 13, 2019, at Nubia Ezza Inyimagu community, in the Izzi Local Government Area of the state.
He was arraigned on one-count charge of murder. According to the Police Prosecutor, Barr Eze, the offence was punishable under section 319(1) of the Criminal Code Cap. 33, Vol. 1, Laws of Ebonyi State, 2009.